  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the automatic detection of safe data reuse patterns in systems with data caches, as investigated by Segarra et al. [67], illustrates the ongoing efforts to refine WCET analysis frameworks to accommodate the complexities introduced by data caching in modern processors.",
    "One of the primary challenges in WCET estimation is accurately measuring and analyzing execution times across different processor cores with distinct characteristics and capabilities.",
    "Traditional static analysis techniques, while reliable, struggle with the dynamic and unpredictable nature of modern hardware, leading to significant overestimations of execution times [68].",
    "This discrepancy has prompted researchers to explore dynamic, measurementbased approaches as a more practical solution for soft real-time systems, where absolute determinism is less critical.",
    "Lisper et al. [69] explore the potential of hybrid WCET analysis methods, which combine measurements with static analysis to enhance or replace detailed low-level static analyses."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
